file=Engineering/cypher/custom/attack-playbooks/assets/attack-class-register.md · ar—:Attack-Class Register — cypher/attack-playbooks=> The classes cypher runs, each with its source. Threat-intel-sourced only; speculative techniques labeled reasoning-based (rule 0.6). Every run is gated by caged-scope. Sources: OWASP Top 10 (web) and OWASP Top 10 for LLM Applications 2025 (genai.owasp.org).\n · tb=\| id \| class \| source \| notes for our targets \| · tb=\|---\|---\|---\|---\| · tb=\| W-A01 \| Broken access control (incl. IDOR / per-object authz) \| OWASP Top 10 \| pairs with aegis's per-object review \| · tb=\| W-A02 \| Cryptographic failures \| OWASP Top 10 \| \| · tb=\| W-A03 \| Injection (SQL/command/template/XSS) \| OWASP Top 10 \| \| · tb=\| W-A04 \| Insecure design \| OWASP Top 10 \| validates aegis's threat model \| · tb=\| W-A05 \| Security misconfiguration \| OWASP Top 10 \| ties to ops/maintenance-hygiene \| · tb=\| W-A06 \| Vulnerable & outdated components \| OWASP Top 10 \| ties to ops CVE intake \| · tb=\| W-A07 \| Auth failures \| OWASP Top 10 \| \| · tb=\| W-A08 \| Software/data integrity failures \| OWASP Top 10 \| supply chain \| · tb=\| W-A09 \| Logging/monitoring failures \| OWASP Top 10 \| ties to ops baselines \| · tb=\| W-A10 \| SSRF \| OWASP Top 10 \| \| · tb=\| id \| class \| source \| our-system target \| · tb=\|---\|---\|---\|---\| · tb=\| L01 \| Prompt injection (direct + INDIRECT via ingested content) \| OWASP LLM 2025 \| poisoned docs/pages/MCP responses our agents read — the real risk \| · tb=\| L02 \| Sensitive information disclosure \| OWASP LLM 2025 \| data exfil through agent outputs \| · tb=\| L03 \| Supply chain \| OWASP LLM 2025 \| poisoned dependencies/models/skills \| · tb=\| L04 \| Data & model poisoning \| OWASP LLM 2025 \| \| · tb=\| L05 \| Improper output handling \| OWASP LLM 2025 \| agent output consumed downstream unsanitized \| · tb=\| L06 \| Excessive agency \| OWASP LLM 2025 \| agent led to use a tool beyond its task \| · tb=\| L07 \| System-prompt leakage \| OWASP LLM 2025 \| \| · tb=\| L08 \| Vector/embedding weaknesses \| OWASP LLM 2025 \| RAG / memory-layer attacks (dana's surface) \| · tb=\| L09 \| Misinformation \| OWASP LLM 2025 \| \| · tb=\| L10 \| Unbounded consumption \| OWASP LLM 2025 \| cost/DoS via agent loops \| · tb=\| id \| target \| maps to \| a "held" result proves \| · tb=\|---\|---\|---\|---\| · tb=\| R1 \| Make an agent act OFF its locked plan \| Rail 1 (plan-lock) \| prompt-injection→deviation is caught \| · tb=\| R2 \| Move data OUT of the sandbox \| Rail 2 (egress) \| exfil fails closed \| · tb=\| R3 \| Steer an agent to run a destructive DB op \| Rail 3 (no agent data writes) \| destructive actions stay human \| · tb=\| R4 \| Get cypher itself to exceed scope \| Rail 4 (the cage) \| the adversary can't self-widen \| · tb=\| id \| class \| source \| status \| · tb=\|---\|---\|---\|---\| · tb=\| <FILL_IN> \| \| [advisory/CVE/paper] \| reasoning-based until sourced (0.6) \|